-- CTC Media’s Russia TV Audience Shares Steady, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-06-07T16:58:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/ctc-media-s-russia-tv-audience-shares-steady-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel remained the fifth most-watched among Russian viewers 18
years and older in the week to June 3 as its audience share was
steady, according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, was at 5.5 percent,
unchanged from the previous week, data researcher TNS-Global
said by e-mail today. CTC’s average daily audience among viewers
4 years old and over was also unchanged at 6.3 percent in the
week to June 3, the data show. CTC remained in fifth place among
viewers 4 years old and over, TNS-Global said.  Russia’s NTV Television was the most watched among both
audience categories. Government-controlled Rossiya-1 was pushed
to the third-most watched slot in both categories after
occupying the most-watched spot in the week to May 27, the data
show.  Pervyi Kanal  had the second-biggest audience in both
categories, the data show. TNT was the fourth-most watched
channel among viewers in both categories, the data showed.  To contact the reporters on this story:
